net.sourceforge.waters.model.base
Class IndexedArrayListProxy

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractCollection
      java.util.AbstractList
          net.sourceforge.waters.model.base.IndexedArrayListProxy
All Implemented Interfaces:
Collection, IndexedCollectionProxy, IndexedListProxy, List, Proxy, RandomAccess
public class IndexedArrayListProxy
extends AbstractList
implements IndexedListProxy, RandomAccess

An array list implementation of the IndexedCollectionProxy interface.

This implementation is based an ArrayList backed by a HashMap to map names to the elements of the list. It therefore provides fast access to elements given their name, while maintaining their order. All elements added to a IndexedArrayListProxy must be of type NamedProxy.

A IndexedArrayListProxy can be used as a primary symbol table for unique elements (UniqueElementProxy), by passing a primary flag to the constructor. In this case, the list only accepts members of type UniqueElementProxy and maintains their symbol table pointer using the joinMap() and leaveMap() methods.

Author:
Robi Malik

equalsWithGeometry

public boolean equalsWithGeometry(Object partner)
Description copied from interface: Proxy
Checks whether two elements are equal and have the same geometry information. This method implements content-based equality, i.e., two elements will be equal if their contents are the same. While the standard equals() method only considers structural contents, this method also takes the layout information of graphical objects such as nodes and edges into account. This method can be very slow for large structures and is intended for testing purposes only.
